name: core_arch::x86::sse2::_mm_div_pd

intrinsics::simd::simd_div.doc:
Divides `lhs` by `rhs` elementwise.

 `T` must be a vector of integers or floats.

 # Safety
 For integers, `rhs` must not contain any zero elements.
 Additionally for signed integers, `<int>::MIN / -1` is undefined behavior.

doc:
Divide packed double-precision (64-bit) floating-point elements in `a` by
 packed elements in `b`.

 [Intel's documentation](https://www.intel.com/content/www/us/en/docs/intrinsics-guide/index.html#text=_mm_div_pd)
